The National Chairman of Accord, Muhammed Lawal Nalado, has declared that the party will defeat the All Progressives Congress (APC) and Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and other political parties in the 2023 general elections in Oyo State. Nalado said during the campaign flag-off of the Oyo North senatorial district candidate of the party, Shina Abiola Peller on Wednesday in Iseyin, Oyo State. Nalado while addressing the gathering said Accord has become more popular than other political parties in the state. He said the popularity of the party will make it defeat all other political parties in the 2023 general elections. He added that the turnout of people during the flag-off was a testimony that the party remains the only party to win the elections in the state. Nalado said, “All our candidates will win the elections. Insha Allah, we will come back here to celebrate the victory of our senatorial candidate and all other candidates in 2023. “Oyo State is home of Accord. We are on ground. And I want to assure you that our senatorial candidate and all other candidates will win the elections because Accord is popular in the state. “We are popular more than any other political parties in the state. “We will defeat candidates of all other political parties in the 2023 general elections. We will win the elections hands down”.